{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is the vision model’s real classification quality plus policy handoff. MOCK-MISS: not just one local function. REAL-INFRA: no OS/subprocess requirement by itself. LLM-DEP: yes, correctness depends on real model judgment of explicitness. MULTI-STEP: single model decision, so not Workflow. Rejected higher level (Workflow) because behavior text describes one moderation judgment, not multiple agentic stages.","test_description":"Submit known explicit images to the real vision moderation model in staging and assert each result is flagged and routed to review queue, with no publish event emitted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is robustness of model output content under adversarial text variants. MOCK-MISS: local parser/unit tests cannot validate semantic moderation quality. LLM-DEP: yes, real text model behavior is the core risk. MULTI-STEP: one classification step, so not Workflow. Rejected higher level (Workflow) because behavior text asks for a single text-check outcome, not chained agentic decisions.","test_description":"Run a corpus of hate-speech variants (leet, homoglyphs, unicode confusables) through the real text moderation model and assert they are flagged and held for review.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode is module handoff/orchestration: two check results -> publish decision/state transition. MOCK-MISS: yes, this behavior can fail when local modules integrate (decision service, queue/repo, publisher). REAL-INFRA: not required; in-process fakes can catch hold/drop/publish routing bugs. LLM-DEP: disqualified by behavior text 'passes both content checks' (model quality not under test). MULTI-STEP agentic chain not required because checks can be stubbed as pass.","test_description":"Wire moderation orchestrator, persistence, and publisher with in-process doubles; force both checks to PASS and assert exactly one publish action occurs, no hold record, and no dropped terminal state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end SLA across multiple agentic steps (vision + text model) plus final decision. REAL-INFRA likely matters (network/model latency), and LLM-DEP exists because real model calls are in path. MULTI-STEP: explicitly yes from behavior text naming sequential pipeline stages. Rejected lower levels because stubs can hide real latency and queueing interactions under peak load.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end load test in staging using real model endpoints for image and text checks; measure submit-to-final-decision latency and assert p95 (or stricter agreed percentile) stays <=5s during peak-like throughput.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior is infrastructure failure handling at external-call boundary. MOCK-HIDE: yes, simple mocks often miss real timeout/error-shape behavior that causes accidental fallback/auto-approve. REAL-INFRA: yes, needs real HTTP failure modes (timeouts/5xx/connection errors) or equivalent system-level fault injection. LLM-DEP: no, content quality is irrelevant. Rejected higher level (Agentic/Workflow) because behavior text is explicitly about unavailability handling, not model judgment.","test_description":"With a real deployed service, induce vision endpoint outages (timeout and 5xx) and assert image submissions are persisted into retry queue with no auto-approval/publish path taken.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Core risk is real model nondeterminism and calibration drift on borderline inputs. LLM-DEP: yes, repeated real vision outputs may vary and drive inconsistent moderation. MOCK-HIDE: deterministic stubs would always pass and hide inconsistency. MULTI-STEP: repeated submissions are repeated evaluations of same decision type, not a multi-stage agent pipeline.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline images repeatedly to the real vision moderation path within a defined window and assert decision consistency rate meets threshold; fail on flapping beyond tolerance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.77,"Workflow":0.08}}]}
